column1: The American people can’t wait any longer. We need more COVID relief. https://t.co/pI5NgLFQ4r

Together we can slow down climate change ensure access to affordable health care recover our economy get Americans back to work and mitigate the lasting impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic. Together we can create a brighter future #VoteBlue

Happy Halloween! 🎃 Halloween looks different this year but it’s important to #WearAMask and socially distance to protect our families and neighbors. Next week we can vote @JoeBiden into office contain COVID-19 and get back to our favorite traditions next year!
Schools and our entire country could have had COVID-19 relief aid back in May if the Senate had passed the Heroes Act. https://t.co/v5lPMeCI5f

The @nytimes estimates @realDonaldTrump's #COVID19 care would cost more than $100000. Not many Americans could afford such a bill & there are cases of bills of $400000. We need to continue the fight for access to affordable health care not take it away. https://t.co/ETlDVZRKMB
With #COVID19 cases rising in Connecticut we must remember this public health crisis is not over. We need to continue to socially distance and #WearAMask to protect our families and neighbors.
President Trump is wrong. COVID won’t go away without a real plan. And he doesn’t have one. #Debates2020

I joined Governor Lamont at Lilly's Soul Food in Windsor earlier this week to announce a new program to help small businesses with federal funding. These programs work! It's time of the Senate to come to the table pass more COVID relief! https://t.co/FVvSWHRQDe

Today instead of taking up either of the two #COVID relief bills the House has passed the Senate is rushing a vote to confirm a #SCOTUS seat. Instead of putting suffering Americans first the Administration and Senate Republicans are putting their politics first.

Our state's #COVID19 cases are rising and teachers are still working hard to educate Connecticut's youngest citizens. The #HeroesAct would provide necessary resources for teacher and student safety and the Senate needs to pass it now!

The #COVID19 pandemic has severely impacted all aspects of life as we must take precautions to keep ourselves family & neighbors safe. The 2 bills the House has passed would provide relief to restaurants- instead they sit collecting dust in the Senate. https://t.co/VOUvFmCJix
President Trump and VP Pence should focus on providing COVID relief to Americans not forcing an extreme Supreme Court nominee through. #Debates2020

74% of voters want the Senate to take on #COVID19 relief before a SCOTUS nominee and @realDonaldTrump just announced he's stopping all talks with Congress so he can do the exact opposite. Americans need help now not after the election! https://t.co/ULvWolPdzd

Melissa Szymanski a teacher in Windsor shared her experience with the high costs of tests associated with #COVID19 and what can be done to improve teacher's ability to get tested. Keeping our teachers healthy and safe must always be a top priority. https://t.co/QOnWJyyJyP
Our family and neighbors with preexisting conditions our seniors and every one of the 200000 people who have died due to #COVID19 are certainly not "nobodies." https://t.co/dMeJqZezPA

The impact of #COVID19 has changed what election season looks like but you should still be involved! Volunteer to phone/text bank make a voting plan with your friends and neighbors or even volunteer for a campaign. You can volunteer for my campaign at https://t.co/vbf1psXG06

Connecticut has worked hard to slow the spread of #COVID19. With cases rising slightly in our state it is important to continue to #WearAMask and physically distance when necessary. Do your part to keep our friends and neighbors safe!

Schools in CT have started classes some with in-person teaching and the Senate has still not passed the #HeroesAct to provide necessary funding! Teachers shouldn't have to provide student's supplies and now they shouldn't have to provide #COVID19 PPE.
Make a plan to vote this year! #Covid19 has changed so much about our lives but it can't change this. Whether you vote in person or by mail make sure your voice is heard at the ballot box!

In October before #COVID19 turned our country upside down @JoeBiden tweeted this. We need a president who will do everything they can to keep Americans safe. These protections and plans could have saved lives. https://t.co/y1KiHozXht
#SmallBusinesses make our communities unique and are the livelihood for families. We must continue to support them and ensure they are strong long after the #COVID19 pandemic has passed.

I supported @rosa_delauro's Childcare is Essential Act because families need that funding in the next #COVID19 relief package. Childcare is #essential in helping families weather the public health crisis!

Millions are still unemployed because of the devastating impact of #COVID19 and Senate Republicans are ready to let the expanded unemployment benefits expire. Americans losing their financial lifeline during this crisis will not help the economy they say they care about!
Connecticut continues to work hard to keep #COVID19 contained. Keep up the good work for our friends neighbors and community! https://t.co/CBNVy0uCsK

The US is topping 60000 new cases of #COVID19 per day. Our state is doing well but we cannot let our guard down. We need real national leadership to get us through this public health crisis. #WearAMask!

No one should be forced to decide between their health and their vote. I voted for the #HeroesAct which includes funding for mail-in ballots. #COVID19 has changed many aspects of our lives but it must not be the reason someone's voice is not heard at the ballot box.

#COVID19 cases are rising across the country causing health and economic devastation. Connecticut has made great progress but we cannot stop here! The House passed the #HeroesAct to offer relief and resources. The Senate must act now!
We must ensure our most vulnerable are protected. 55% of COVID-19 deaths in Connecticut were in nursing facilities.
COVID-19 doesn’t stop if testing for the virus slows. Keep getting tested. Keep wearing a mask. Keep your family and neighbors safe.
Provisions in the CARES Act have provided states with resources to expand access to COVID-19 testing. Use these resources and get tested! Find a site here: https://t.co/YxeIlfnHhy

We must expand healthcare access & ensure even after the COVID-19 pandemic everyone receives the care they need. It is unacceptable this admin. is still trying to take healthcare away from millions- as we watch the tragic impact of the COVID-19 pandemic. https://t.co/2hk3Ln2F6x
Because CT has taken COVID-19 seriously we are making great progress in containing the virus. Keep wearing your mask and social distancing! https://t.co/6iTEysiL9f
If you have recovered from COVID-19 please consider donating your plasma! https://t.co/EFfS9nyqE0
ICYMI: I joined the Real Story to discuss my thoughts on how we should address the COVID-19 pandemic and the economic challenges it has brought on. https://t.co/4dFrQUbGM0
Good work CT. Please continue to social distance and stay home! https://t.co/r1X9pql4ow
